Rating: 3
This recipe is very similar to one in one of Marcella Hazan's books, and I adopted two simple ideas from her that I think are worth considering. First, the ricotta shouldn't be added in a dollop; it should be mixed into the hot pasta. It adds a wonderful consistency that connects the vegetables to the pasta. Second, she uses freshly grated pecorino romano to add zip to the dish, which is exactly what it needs. There were no leftovers in my house, and indeed, my family fought (politely) over the last morsels.

