Rating: 3
I really enjoyed this recipe. I'm a huge fan of eggplant! I did doctor the recipe a little. I used crushed tomatoes instead of whole, creating a smoother sauce. I increased the garlic to about 3 cloves. I added a little bit of red pepper flakes. I also increased the olive oil and added a bit of red wine (didn't use water). I put a dollop of ricotta on each serving, but my husband and I agreed it didn't need it and really only added calories and fat. I added the 2TBS of fresh basil, but next time I'd increase that as well. Overall, a pretty simple vegetarian dish for a weeknight.

